article.headline: Jones' 18 points help Central Connecticut State take down Holy Cross 78-67
article.description: — Jordan Jones had 18 points in Central Connecticut State's 78-67 victory over Holy Cross on Saturday.
article.linkText: Jones' 18 points help Central Connecticut State take down Holy Cross 78-67
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- — Jordan Jones had 18 points in Central Connecticut State's 78-67 victory over Holy Cross on Saturday. Jones shot 6 of 11 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line for the Blue Devils (3-4). Allan Jeanne-Rose added 14 points and three blocks and Kellen Amos scored 12 points. Joseph Octave finished with 24 points and six rebounds for the Crusaders (2-7). Holy Cross got nine points from Will Batchelder, and Caleb Kenney finished with eight points and 11 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
